WEBVTT

00:00:03.750 --> 00:00:09.333
Continuing on the Define Class page,
go to the Pricing Information section.

00:00:09.333 --> 00:00:15.708
For this section, we will leave all information as-is
since none of our products have fees in Saba.

00:00:15.708 --> 00:00:24.583
Under the Registration Information section: Identify how many registrations the class delivery can accommodate.

00:00:24.583 --> 00:00:29.166
Type in the Maximum participants in the Max Count field.

00:00:29.166 --> 00:00:36.041
Select the Pick Vendor icon to view the Vendor pop up Window
and select Search to populate a vendor list.

00:00:36.041 --> 00:00:41.208
The Vendor identifies which virtual platform
will be used for the session.

00:00:41.208 --> 00:00:46.666
Select the Vendor that will be used
as the Virtual platform for this session.

00:00:46.666 --> 00:00:49.958
Once the Vendor is selected, the pop-up window will close

00:00:49.958 --> 00:00:54.166
and bring you back to the Registration Information section.

00:00:54.166 --> 00:01:00.708
Select the Pick Customer Service Rep icon to open
the Search Person, Internal pop-up window.

00:01:00.708 --> 00:01:07.041
The Customer Service Rep is responsible
for the details and content related to this class.

00:01:07.041 --> 00:01:12.416
Please note that this may differ from the course owner,
as it may be a different team in charge of deliveries

00:01:12.416 --> 00:01:19.500
and this field will be displayed on the Saba notification
that the learner receives when they register to a class.

00:01:19.500 --> 00:01:24.208
A GD mailbox is required to be added as point of contact.

00:01:24.208 --> 00:01:29.916
Add the beginning of the email address
in the First Name field and select Search.

00:01:29.916 --> 00:01:32.583
In the People section, under the Select column,

00:01:32.583 --> 00:01:35.708
select the mailbox to be added.

00:01:35.708 --> 00:01:38.833
Once it has been selected,
the pop-up window will close,

00:01:38.833 --> 00:01:43.416
and it will bring you back to the Registration Information section.

00:01:43.416 --> 00:01:49.000
For the section “Allow Drop”,
you will have to select one of the following options:

00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:52.250
By default, it is set to Yes.

00:01:52.250 --> 00:01:56.291
Yes, this class can be dropped anytime after registration, or;

00:01:56.291 --> 00:02:00.083
No, this class cannot be dropped after registration.

00:02:00.083 --> 00:02:04.125
Under the Availability Information section:

00:02:04.125 --> 00:02:10.041
Leave the Display for Call Centre and Display for learner unchecked, as the Learning Infrastructure Team will determine

00:02:10.041 --> 00:02:16.500
with the Saba administrator if the options should be enabled
to display the class in the Saba catalog.

00:02:16.500 --> 00:02:20.208
Add a date in the Open Enrollment date field.

00:02:20.208 --> 00:02:23.000
Add a date in the Enrollment close on field, and;

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:30.291
Leave the Class Completion Reminder after
End Date (days) field to 14, set automatically by the system.

00:02:30.291 --> 00:02:33.791
Under the Meetings Details section:

00:02:33.791 --> 00:02:40.375
Keep the VLE Provider field as
Non Integrated VLE Provider – it must not be modified.

00:02:40.375 --> 00:02:44.083
If you do not add the Guest attend URL hyperlink in Saba,

00:02:44.083 --> 00:02:48.458
you must add “To follow” in each of the remaining fields.

00:02:48.458 --> 00:02:53.625
When learners receive their registration confirmation,
this will be included in the notification

00:02:53.625 --> 00:02:58.458
and will let learners know that
the link to the session will be sent later.

00:02:58.458 --> 00:03:05.791
If you have the virtual URL and you want to add it,
you can add the URL in the Guest Attend URL field.

00:03:05.791 --> 00:03:13.833
Select Finish at the bottom of the page to save your class information, the class ID will then be generated automatically.

00:03:13.833 --> 00:03:19.875
After saving your class information, the class ID
is generated and can be found next to the Class ID field

00:03:19.875 --> 00:03:24.041
in the Class Details section and at the end of the class title.

00:03:24.041 --> 00:03:27.708
If a class description has been added, you must Internationalize it

00:03:27.708 --> 00:03:33.333
by selecting the Internationalize
icon located on the upper right of the main page.

00:03:33.333 --> 00:03:36.958
The translate pop-up window will display.

00:03:36.958 --> 00:03:43.625
In the Locale field, use the drop-down arrow
to select the other official language you must translate.

00:03:43.625 --> 00:03:46.833
In the Description field, erase the original description

00:03:46.833 --> 00:03:51.333
and type the translated text in the other official language.

00:03:51.333 --> 00:03:57.208
In the example, a description was added,
I will erase it and type it in French.

00:03:57.208 --> 00:04:00.541
Select Save to add the translation.

00:04:00.541 --> 00:04:04.625
The Main tab is now complete.

